Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Provide u64 read for 32-bits arch helper

References: bnc#1202494 (Scheduler functional and performance backports)
Patch-mainline: v6.0-rc1
Git-commit: d05b43059dfa115037cd37bc276a8316391def28

Introducing macro helpers u64_u32_{store,load}() to factorize lockless
accesses to u64 variables for 32-bits architectures.

Users are for now cfs_rq.min_vruntime and sched_avg.last_update_time. To
accommodate the later where the copy lies outside of the structure
(cfs_rq.last_udpate_time_copy instead of sched_avg.last_update_time_copy),
use the _copy() version of those helpers.

Those new helpers encapsulate smp_rmb() and smp_wmb() synchronization and
therefore, have a small penalty for 32-bits machines in set_task_rq_fair()
and init_cfs_rq().

